Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.51,0:00:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you see Hobbes, you see all the great names of history, and then you see
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.89,0:01:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Immanuel Kant who set up the categories, the categories of abstraction, and all
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.85,0:01:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the time on television you hear people violate the various levels, they violate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.55,0:01:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the various levels. Here's the great names, Sir Isaac Newton, so there's three
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.13,0:01:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting geniuses, Sigmund Freud calibrates at 499, Sir Isaac Newton
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.99,0:01:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 499, who is Z equals something, C squared? Einstein at 499, all
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.33,0:01:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of them. See because at 500 there's a new paradigm. You move from that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.62,0:01:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,supposedly objective logical sequential to the subjective, which is not provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.80,0:01:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Advanced spiritual truth then is not provable because it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.49,0:01:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,different paradigm. That which is provable is not spiritual truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.39,0:01:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are always in competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.27,0:02:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you would be stating something within the limitation of the dualistic Newtonian paradigm, which is linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.56,0:02:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual reality is non-linear, not provable, not demonstrable, subjectively experiential, and hugely transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.70,0:02:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Even one or two mild spiritual experiences, whoa, not to mention a near-death experience or something transformative like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.90,0:02:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Which totally changes you forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Near-death experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.40,0:02:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is as far as the human psyche goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.79,0:02:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sophocles, the great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.01,0:02:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The great names of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.21,0:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I was a kid, Socrates was my hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.56,0:02:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, of course, didn't write anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.78,0:02:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, his teachings are well described in Plato, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.85,0:03:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates calibrates at 512.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.57,0:03:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He was, to me, a great spiritual teacher, one of my heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.78,0:03:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, actually, was willing to die for truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.36,0:03:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the days of Socrates, there wasn't the Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.34,0:03:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhism was on the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.48,0:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hindu sages were on the other side of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.86,0:03:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And, therefore, in a really, in a way, non-religious society, Socrates intuited truth at the level of 540, unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.94,0:03:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And Socrates, when he was accused of perverting the minds of youth by teaching them the kind of things I'm teaching today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.46,0:03:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my hemlock, by the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.18,0:03:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Either had to change what he was teaching or drink the hemlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:03:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates chose hemlock rather than violate the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates chose death rather than physical life because of his alignment with truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.09,0:04:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,One of Socrates' best sayings is a very useful one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.21,0:04:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And, pragmatically, for all of us on an almost daily basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, even now, with the coming elections, it's very good to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.82,0:04:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates said something that really resolves just about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Man only chooses the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.71,0:04:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Man always chooses the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.89,0:04:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he can only choose that which he envisions as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.06,0:04:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The only trouble is he doesn't know which is the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.36,0:04:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And he chooses the temporary and illusory rather than the infinite and perpetual.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.84,0:04:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, his intention is always to choose what he feels to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.33,0:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What he thinks to be the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, it might be killing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.16,0:04:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Blowing up a busload of children.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.68,0:05:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But, he believes that it is for the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So that sort of seconds man's intrinsic innocence because the Buddha, Krishna, and Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.17,0:05:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,every great being that ever lived, said man only has one defect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.55,0:05:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.19,0:05:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know the good from the bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.31,0:05:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.83,0:05:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks that it's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.33,0:05:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So he votes for illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.63,0:05:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He sacrifices his life for illusion because he cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the incredible gift that we have right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time in the evolution of all of time, we can tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but within an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.99,0:05:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. Think of the positive karma of a group like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.83,0:05:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,People on the earth today now, for the first time, can tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.82,0:05:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Man only chooses the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So those of us who look favorably on the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.90,0:06:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the Course in Miracles is based on forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how can you forgive people if they're wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.34,0:06:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the question that always arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.57,0:06:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they're bad and evil, how can you forgive people if they're wrong, bad, and evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.76,0:06:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They saw that, was that killing you was to their highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.76,0:06:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that they get to go to heaven, and 3,000 kids get to be blown up in a bus is the price of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.84,0:06:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,would seem to us an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.74,0:06:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But perhaps to their extreme viewpoint, that is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.02,0:06:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore, we can see the innate innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.99,0:06:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because each of us, then, is born with hardware, the hardware,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.36,0:06:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and then superimposed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:06:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Superimposed on that is software.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.78,0:07:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the hardware cannot protect itself against the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.26,0:07:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind is like the hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.96,0:07:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it gets programmed with software.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.79,0:07:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That when you try to put falsity into it, it goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.75,0:07:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.58,0:07:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.70,0:07:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can see that instead of evil and hatred,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps compassion for the tragedy of ignorance,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.98,0:07:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the tragedy of ignorance costs the lives of 10 million, 10 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.07,0:07:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the calibrated levels of the great books of the Western world calibrate around 450 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.65,0:07:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you remove this guy here, Karl Marx, the whole collective total comes out at 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.60,0:07:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty with the recent world and today's social world is the perpetrator-victim model,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the dualistic creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.98,0:07:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx had an unresolved...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.48,0:07:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,method of a complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.02,0:08:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And he revolted against the leading philosopher of his day, Hegel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.82,0:08:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When Hegel's basic teachings was that of the absolute,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.05,0:08:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what you saw that he demonstrated is the influence of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.25,0:08:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field of consciousness, which is what we consult with kinesiology all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.97,0:08:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is the absolute field.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.53,0:08:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel said,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.55,0:08:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,all are accountable because of the principle of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if there's anything that Eagleton...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.58,0:08:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ego hates is to hear that it's not God. The ego secretly thinks it is God, and it hates God and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.96,0:08:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,disguises that hatred in many forms. At least the secularists are honest. They hate God, and the word
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.14,0:08:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,makes them very nervous and upset, so they want to remove it. At least they're honest about it, you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.08,0:08:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,see. The ego is more clever than that. It gets rid of God by getting rid of the sovereignty of the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.03,0:09:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute, the sovereignty of the absolute. It's the sovereignty of the absolute that the core of the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.71,0:09:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissistic ego hates, and the ego hates God. So, Marx had an unresolved, edible complex. I speak as a,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.17,0:09:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I did 50 years of psychoanalysis and psychiatry, was psychoanalyzed by myself, one of the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.17,0:09:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,world's most famous and best. Deep within the unconscious, there is a hatred of that which
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.30,0:09:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,represents authority, the father figure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.37,0:09:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If your experience with your father was benign, you see authority as friendly and protective. If your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,experience or your image, not necessarily your reality experience, at least your image of your father, was
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,threatening, then you confuse authority with authoritarianism, and you hate all authority because you think
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.20,0:09:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it's authoritarian, and you fail to see the legitimacy of true authority. For one thing, information, fact, and
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.67,0:10:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge is itself an authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.09,0:10:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the current relativistic philosophers even hate science and logic, you know, the problematic hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.84,0:10:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You first heard it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.29,0:10:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The probabilistic hermeneutics of relativistic epistemology is why the classroom of America, which used to calibrate in the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,1800s, it now calibrates to about 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.92,0:10:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The denigration of logic, reason, the discipline that goes with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.56,0:11:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so, anyway, because of Marx's unresolved Oedipal Complex, he, which I say is a fact, resist, he was his Oedipal Complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.10,0:11:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,resist. Okay, just check my psychoanalysts, see if he's right. I sweated it out on couch, so I mean I'm screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.50,0:11:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, just check my psychoanalysts, see if he's right. I sweated it out on couch, so I mean I'm screaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.86,0:11:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially. You know, 50 years of psychiatry, nobody ever came in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that didn't have an Oedipal complex or so on. He would be from a different planet
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.94,0:11:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because you grow up with parents, so you're going to see one view as the maternal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.92,0:11:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,permissive, all-inclusive, non-judgmental, and then you're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.06,0:11:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,see the father figure that says, yes, that's nice, but
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.24,0:11:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if you've got a job, you've got to go to work every day. You just can't call in and say, I don't feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,going to work today. You won't have a job on Monday. The maternal
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.82,0:11:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is permissive and inclusive, and the paternal stands
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,more for the survival in the external world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Hegel was the authority father figure,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.59,0:11:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and its impact, this unresolved Oedipal complex here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.23,0:11:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,has impacted all of life in our current society.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.75,0:12:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That error, that error of failure
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.13,0:12:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth, that fallacy, has cost tens of millions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.99,0:12:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of lives have been slaughtered by the error of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.60,0:12:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,projecting, rest in turn, seeing perpetrator and victim
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,out there in the world. There is no perpetrator and victim out there in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.45,0:12:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything comes about as a consequence of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.31,0:12:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,plus your karma and your calibrated level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you turn everything into perpetrator and victim? You'll see that's today's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.90,0:12:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,social contention, the whole litiginous, sociologic
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.72,0:12:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A disaster sees everything as innocent victim and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.81,0:12:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,wicked perpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.17,0:12:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No such thing exists in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.26,0:12:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a perception projected onto society.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.84,0:13:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A company moves into town, theology of Wisconsin, and their
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.40,0:13:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,county company at heine's ball or other poor little farmer
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.05,0:13:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.55,0:13:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now people, they're crops are bought instantly, whole crop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.64,0:13:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The company makes money because they're maping their future to a new type of farming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.04,0:13:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they've got inexpensive labor and they're right there in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.92,0:13:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,where the growing fields are the town prospers people now can buy cars they
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.49,0:13:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,can afford telephones and they put down electricity electricity down one side of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.21,0:13:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the highway and company makes money and people invest in the company and the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,consumer gets products on the field you don't have to can all your own peas so I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,worked there and you got paid a nickel an hour for everything extra over 12
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.71,0:13:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,hours 30 cents an hour and if you work more than 12 hours you got 35 cents
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.77,0:14:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody was happy I was happy I had an income the town was happy the company
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.38,0:14:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,was happy then how do you find a perpetrator and victim in there you have
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.90,0:14:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that as a belief system now you walk into the town you say well look the
