Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.92,0:15:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reliable source of discerning truth and falsehood the kinesiologic method is the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.16,0:15:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,first way 135 is way down from truth isn't it what truth is at 200 135 is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.29,0:15:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,way down now you've got huge countries
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.69,0:15:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,China Russia giant countries being run by a consciousness level belief system at
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.57,0:15:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,135 135 brings death destruction paranoia the KGB the secret police
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,secret killings brings pull pot or pot pull whatever that is name is pull pot
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.74,0:15:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,pull went to pot potty pull I don't know what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.50,0:16:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean yet you know we're not just speaking academically today talking
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.56,0:16:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,about the lives of tens of millions of people in my lifetime died for
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.56,0:16:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood tens of millions tens of millions died for falsehood the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,inability to discern truth from falsehood hmm
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.03,0:16:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all right so here's the content here's the proximate field years the internet
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.68,0:16:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,field so here's the Internet field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.64,0:16:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,infinitely power. This is powerful. This is what we consult with kinesiology. This is the absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the absolute, which is infinite. This statement calibrates so far. So this is the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.31,0:16:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute spoken of by Hegel and which would give Karl Marx nightmares if he was reborn today,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.43,0:17:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'd say this is the criteria of truth and not your narcissistic ego. This is the proximate
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.92,0:17:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,field. The second naivete is any statement is only true within a stated context. The naivete of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.34,0:17:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,human mind, it thinks only in terms of limitation. This is not a great diagram, but we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,make a better one. We were going to make a better diagram. Anyway, this is the linear definable
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.38,0:17:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,world of Newtonian.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In science, you can measure it. This is the field of the scientific reductionist, the materialistic
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.36,0:17:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,reductionist. Unless you can measure it, weigh it, score it, it's not real. This is the linear
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,statement that so-and-so is true, that so-and-so lied, so-and-so didn't lie, et cetera, that a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,certain law violates human rights or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.53,0:18:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The statement is only true within a certain context. That's true under this context. It is not true
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.99,0:18:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,on another context. The rules that apply to the population in times of war are quite different than
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.98,0:18:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the ones that apply in times of peace. It's confused. So truth is only true if you state in what
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.54,0:18:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,context, in what context. So the context then is the proximate field. The proximate field is the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.39,0:18:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions, climate, population, wealth, a thousand things. A thing is only true under certain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.01,0:18:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions. The conditions which the naive mind thinks are causal, they're not causal. They're just
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.02,0:18:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions. Rain and humidity and barometric pressure and altitude. If you try to find the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.43,0:19:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,cause of anything within the Newtonian paradigm of cause and effect, you will find that every single
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.79,0:19:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,event, supposed event, has an infinite number of causes, that the world of causality is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.02,0:19:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say, what is the cause of this little speck of dust being here right now? Well, it depends on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.28,0:19:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the barometric pressure, the ozone, depends on the altitude, depends on the wind speed, it depends on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.80,0:19:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what time of the year, it depends on temperature, barometric pressure. It would have to occur in a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.36,0:19:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,building, so somebody would have to create this building for this little piece of dust to be here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.68,0:19:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and this building requires a state to be in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.88,0:19:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Which requires a globe, which requires a universe. So you can see a complete explanation of why this
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.98,0:19:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,little piece of dust is right here. The number of factors is infinite, infinite, infinite. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.07,0:19:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you will realize that you're dealing in an illusion. There is no cause for it to be, because phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.90,0:19:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are like clouds appearing in the sky. The cloud appears as a consequence of the totality of the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.98,0:20:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,environment, condensing and presenting itself thusly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.30,0:20:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no cause for a cloud. No cause. No cause. It's not caused. It's the consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.86,0:20:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When all factors are favorable, then it emerges spontaneously of its own. And when they're not, it fades away
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.30,0:20:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own. You say, well, the wind is causing it. The wind's not causing it, there's wind there all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.80,0:20:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is the infinite contact which we can solve, the absolute, when we consult with kinesiologists.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.34,0:20:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, as compared to the absolute, this calibrates as so much. Okay, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.79,0:20:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The content field and context, this is just in words. The content in the center is limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.88,0:20:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the ego, the linear, definable, measurable, and it deals in force.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.91,0:21:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite field deals in power. Force moves from here to there. Consequently, force always creates
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.97,0:21:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,counter-force.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.97,0:21:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As Napoleon and everybody else has found out through history, forcing people to do things results in counter-force.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.93,0:21:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If it evolves as a consequence of the field, then it has no enemies, because now it's coming out of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.93,0:21:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And power is aligned with truth. Therefore, that which is truthful, then, and integrous, eventually influences
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.93,0:21:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,what is witnessed within the world, but not in a cause and effect way. It may be delayed over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.66,0:21:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because truth then begins to set a context by which everything is measured. Everything is measured by.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.24,0:21:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And its effect may be slow. So, force is quick and temporary. Power is slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.78,0:22:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, force is like hitting something, and power is like gravity. Gravity just stands there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.97,0:22:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, force, you have to constantly feed it energy. It's always wearing out. You have to feed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.97,0:22:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Military supplies, battle, money, tax money, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.16,0:22:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Force then exhausts itself and creates counter-force.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.39,0:22:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Power then just merely stands there, controls everything within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.65,0:22:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Every iron filing within the gravitational field is at the effect of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.65,0:22:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no opposition. It has no opposite. So, truth has no opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.74,0:22:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no opposite to truth. There is only its absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.22,0:22:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.02,0:22:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,With the kinesiologic response, what you see is in the presence of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.02,0:23:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy flows down the acupuncture system. The body goes instantly strong in the presence of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.22,0:23:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like protoplasm recognizes that which is supportive of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.57,0:23:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the presence of falsehood, the arm goes weak because protoplasm, on an even physical level,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.73,0:23:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,protoplasm knows what is inimicable to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.73,0:23:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The amoeba goes towards that which supports its survival. It withdraws.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.73,0:23:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Even protoplasm, which is an impersonal response.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.73,0:23:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the kinesiologic response is impersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.87,0:23:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The proximate field is the spiritual ego. It's semi-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.87,0:23:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to be random.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.00,0:23:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's definable not within the Newtonian, but more by non-linear dynamics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.00,0:23:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The field tends to quickly do a thing like, see what it did again?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.00,0:23:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't watch it, it'll just fly out by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.00,0:23:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to tuck it in someplace, make it stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.10,0:24:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unpredictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.02,0:24:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme sports. I always say something about extreme sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.02,0:24:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not trying to keep them alive past their time to leave this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.02,0:24:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.40,0:24:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But so you understand non-linear dynamics,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.58,0:24:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that after 32 jumps from the plane,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.70,0:24:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,number 33 is coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.70,0:24:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the non-linear dynamics.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.70,0:24:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of regularity, unpredictably comes non-regularity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.86,0:24:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that computer chip had an error in the 26th decimal point?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.86,0:24:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody in the audience always remembers the name of that chip.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.86,0:24:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that? It was about 25 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.46,0:24:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Intel?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.87,0:24:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. There was an error in the 26th decimal point.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.87,0:24:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And people said,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.87,0:24:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,how often is the 26th decimal point going to come up?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.87,0:24:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.90,0:25:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that by iteration, meaning repetition,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.90,0:25:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,millions and millions of times,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.90,0:25:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,26th decimal point can only change the whole course of civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.90,0:25:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.90,0:25:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.06,0:25:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So non-linear dynamics.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.06,0:25:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I always bring that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.86,0:25:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the infinite context we call spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.86,0:25:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, linear, unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.86,0:25:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's purely experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.86,0:25:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.86,0:25:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's self-existent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.90,0:25:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.82,0:25:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's knowable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.82,0:25:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.82,0:25:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-local.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.82,0:25:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.82,0:25:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So just so we define the different context.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.82,0:25:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual foundation is a novelty in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.86,0:25:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the world I grew up, it's the way the world was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.86,0:25:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In Wisconsin, this is the way everybody was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.94,0:25:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Chicago, by the way, calibrates at 440.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.94,0:25:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you have an adolescent child who's lost himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.20,0:25:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and has to go someplace on the planet to find himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.20,0:26:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd suggest he go to Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.86,0:26:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than Afghanistan or some place.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.46,0:26:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the virtues.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.46,0:26:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to see how important they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.46,0:26:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They sound like, so what homilies, homilies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.46,0:26:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, in the world I grew up, everybody was this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.46,0:26:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody went to Boy Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.46,0:26:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody went to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.46,0:26:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was the Girl Scout.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.46,0:26:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody belonged to the 4-H club.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.46,0:26:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was honest, reliable, and integrity, and polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.46,0:26:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was cordial.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.46,0:26:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody did their homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.14,0:26:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Fairness was okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.14,0:26:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we take these for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.14,0:26:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You think everybody in the world is considerate, responsible, moral, warm, kind, easygoing, tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.20,0:26:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to control your temper.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.20,0:26:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't ramble off all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.20,0:26:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.20,0:26:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You meet somebody, you say, how do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.20,0:26:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People are orderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.20,0:26:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't either slobby mess every place they go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.20,0:26:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick up after yourself, young men.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.20,0:26:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We take these for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.36,0:27:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole segments of society do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.36,0:27:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not pick up after themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.36,0:27:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,One glimpse of a sidewalk anywhere in any big city, I can tell you what the caliber, level, consciousness of that city is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.45,0:27:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.45,0:27:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody I grew up with was sane, fair, ethical.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.24,0:27:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,People tried to stay healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.24,0:27:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They were faithful.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.24,0:27:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody had a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.24,0:27:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They were rational.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.24,0:27:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was reasonable or not reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.24,0:27:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's intention was benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.24,0:27:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,People were honorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.24,0:27:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,People were automatically protective.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.24,0:27:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had a little kid with you, you protected it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.24,0:27:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was somebody else's little kid, everybody was protective of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.24,0:27:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You tried to steer around the cat in the road and not run over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.72,0:27:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was humane.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.72,0:27:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If the animal was sick and aged and in suffering and pain, you tried to put it to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.72,0:27:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to do it, but you did it because you loved the animal, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.17,0:27:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's interested in being pleasing and happy and glad and positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.17,0:28:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,People were generally the salt of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.17,0:28:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They tend to be modest, diplomatic, polite.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.20,0:28:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People are just sort of automatically nice to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.20,0:28:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the world of the 200s and the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.20,0:28:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The 200s and the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.20,0:28:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's positive emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.58,0:28:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all emotion, but these are not positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.06,0:28:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,From this, you can create a whole different life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.06,0:28:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think of the large segments of the world's populations that do not express these,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.30,0:28:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,they do not express these attitudes at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.37,0:28:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our failure of diplomatic relations with such countries is that we assume they're this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.37,0:28:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.50,0:28:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They think being honest is stupid, honorable is dumb, completely the opposite of what we believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.10,0:28:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get to that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.52,0:29:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the virtues and their effect on brain physiology is what we have to get to.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.52,0:29:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to move into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.81,0:29:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.81,0:29:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We said the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.29,0:29:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This mind, this thing is magnetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.74,0:29:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that something?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.77,0:29:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People say I try to meditate, I try to contemplate, but my mind is busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.48,0:29:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, your mind is not busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.54,0:29:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind, this is where your mind is, is silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.58,0:29:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 1% of your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.96,0:29:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you think is your mind is 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.47,0:29:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.73,0:29:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to meditate, but my mind just won't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.02,0:29:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What won't stop is 1% of your mind is speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.02,0:29:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know it's speaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.59,0:30:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the silence of the 99%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.75,0:30:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize if it wasn't for the silence of the woods, you couldn't hear the birds song, could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.14,0:30:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the fact that your mind is blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.71,0:30:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.71,0:30:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you can see the A.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.71,0:30:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason you can see this A
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.74,0:30:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of the whiteness of the blackboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.74,0:30:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.02,0:30:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If this was all jammed up with stuff, you couldn't read A.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.02,0:30:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so you're already quite well advanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.50,0:30:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of your mind is already silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.82,0:30:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And the 1% is speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.82,0:30:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for the 99% being silent, you wouldn't know what the 1% was saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.82,0:30:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And the difficulty is not that you have a busy mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.20,0:30:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but you are hypnotized by the 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.84,0:30:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Having heard that, you're already somewhat liberated from its dominance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.03,0:31:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You think this is a huge mind full of all kinds of stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.34,0:31:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you ever clear it out in a hundred lifetimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.34,0:31:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.56,0:31:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is 99% silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.56,0:31:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,1% is speaking or imaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.39,0:31:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you've done is fallen into a hypnotic trance at the 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.15,0:31:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You are hypnotized and in a trance by the 1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.15,0:31:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's a silent population, one person talks,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.47,0:31:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be dominated by that one person who talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.47,0:31:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.47,0:31:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not going to listen to the fact that 999 of the people in this population are silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.95,0:31:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one idiot chair-ringing away.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.95,0:31:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you're going to say, he is the genius and they're the dumb ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.46,0:31:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I will listen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.46,0:31:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows how to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.46,0:32:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.46,0:32:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You folks are non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.58,0:32:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I will listen to the linear and ignore the non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.10,0:32:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I will pay attention to the one frog in the ocean and ignore the entire ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.26,0:32:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I think the whole ocean is full of frogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.26,0:32:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just this little frog here, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.26,0:32:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This little frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.26,0:32:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The ocean is not full of frogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.67,0:32:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's full of not-frogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.41,0:32:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now how does this 1% keep you in its grip?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.41,0:32:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In its thrall, you know, in its thralldom?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.41,0:32:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it gain its power and dominance over you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.41,0:32:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because it politicizes everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.57,0:32:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What would we watch at 5 o'clock or 6 o'clock on TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.57,0:32:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It politicizes, moralizes, idealizes, hypothesizes, romanticizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.57,0:32:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that be wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.57,0:33:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Criticizes, emotionalizes, dramatizes, fantasizes, prizes, theorizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.08,0:33:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is the silence gets eyes to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.08,0:33:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's always izing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.08,0:33:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypnotizing, victimizing, theorizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.08,0:33:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfecture to victimizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.08,0:33:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.36,0:33:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.36,0:33:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is held within consciousness and then it seems to be experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.36,0:33:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks the cause is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.36,0:33:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, the concept is being held in consciousness and demonstrates out in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.00,0:33:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is then the effect, the final result.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.26,0:33:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the mind itself tends to have lower mind and higher mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.26,0:33:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 people mentate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.26,0:33:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They mentate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.51,0:33:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.51,0:33:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They mentate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.51,0:33:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But they think they think.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.70,0:33:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there's a calibrated lower mind in esoteric psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.70,0:33:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates at about 155.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.70,0:33:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the one that the politician aims for.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.70,0:34:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.70,0:34:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The politician politician is trying to stir up your feelings and avoid reason, logic, and proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.70,0:34:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It can just accuse something of something and stir up the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.57,0:34:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It tries to avoid higher mind, which values truth, logic, and proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.57,0:34:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.70,0:34:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Say if somebody's a crook, you've got to have evidence that he's a crook and that he stole it, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.70,0:34:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So this side is higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.70,0:34:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.70,0:34:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more diffuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.70,0:34:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's appreciative of the beauties of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.73,0:34:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It has power rather than...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.73,0:34:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He relies on the power of truth rather than force.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.79,0:34:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more open.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.79,0:34:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And we say that those people are more evolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.79,0:34:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the purpose of education is to move people out of just emotionalizing about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.79,0:34:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be a human to emotionalize about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.34,0:35:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Just emotionalizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.34,0:35:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Just thinking about them, reflecting on them, beginning to get what the inference and the meaning is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.34,0:35:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.34,0:35:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.30,0:35:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Power of Intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.74,0:35:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the name's new book called, The Power of Intention?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.22,0:35:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wayne Dyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.54,0:35:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wayne Dyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.54,0:35:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.54,0:35:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, I read the last chapter because you could get it free off the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.54,0:35:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The Power of Intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.54,0:35:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.02,0:35:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said that this is how things come about.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.02,0:35:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of intention, the field manifests as a consequence of intention of the infinite potentiality becoming an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.02,0:35:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So the need for a pointer actualizes a pointer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.02,0:35:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the need.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.02,0:35:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The need of the pointer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.02,0:36:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the person who had the pointer also had an intentionality to be useful of service or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.02,0:36:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So the intentionalities came together.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.02,0:36:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it manifested as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.68,0:36:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics demonstrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.68,0:36:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I put it in because there's a certain kind of a scientific, intellectualized, educated mind that objects to spirituality, you know, that it's not logical, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.86,0:36:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we show how to go from the most primitive up through the evolution of mankind and consciousness up to thinkingness up through the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.40,0:36:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And from the Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.40,0:36:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You then have to move into 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.40,0:36:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But to get there, you have to move out of the lock-in of the Newtonian paradigm, dualistic, definable over this causing of that on a one-to-one basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.40,0:36:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One-to-one basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.40,0:37:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way out, the way you can still be logical and be spiritual is to move into what happened to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.40,0:37:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.40,0:37:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.40,0:37:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to our last line?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.58,0:37:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.58,0:37:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.65,0:37:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is to move into nonlinear dynamics and quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.65,0:37:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the reason that it's important for us is because we talk about the power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.84,0:37:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, we're talking about the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.84,0:37:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The state of the world is definable right at this instant via the Schrodinger equations, which are quite complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.84,0:37:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, they're not complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.84,0:37:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you understand them, they're simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.84,0:37:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But they are both time-dependent and time-independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.84,0:37:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the state, the potentiality of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.84,0:37:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, what a thing could be in the next instant depends on what it is right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.84,0:37:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the state of this world right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.16,0:38:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then by intention, which you hold in consciousness, what happens is you cannot do the same experiment twice because having done it once, you've already changed the conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.16,0:38:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the consequence is the Dirac equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.19,0:38:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle then is the introduction of the power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.64,0:38:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Many things can come out of a situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.70,0:38:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But because of your intention and the collective intention of other people, you collapse the potentiality, so-called you collapse the wave function, and the potential now becomes the actual.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.21,0:38:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the collective intention of wide numbers of people has a determining effect on what actually precipitates in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.30,0:38:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our combined intention is influencing the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.78,0:38:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The combined intention of this group here, which is a very powerful group, is within the 15%, which is influencing what is happening within the world and is supporting the evolution of consciousness, which is now over 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.81,0:39:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.10,0:39:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the potential of consciousness to move ahead is moved ahead by spiritually oriented people.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.10,0:39:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And people who are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.22,0:39:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't call themselves spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.22,0:39:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They just call themselves honest, hardworking, and pay their taxes, and take care of their family and kids, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.42,0:39:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't call that spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.42,0:39:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But those are, as you can see, those are the very basics of spirituality, is responsibility, accountability, commitment to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.42,0:39:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll finish with this, certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.62,0:39:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, once you, because of intention now, the world has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.51,0:39:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, you move from.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.67,0:39:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is defined, calculable by the Schrodinger equations to the Dirac equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.40,0:39:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dirac equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.40,0:39:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's a potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.40,0:40:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you, through intention, you change it into an actual.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.59,0:40:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This comes from the Schrodinger equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.62,0:40:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is now the Dirac equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.62,0:40:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dirac equations now define what are the new Schrodinger equations, the new condition of the universe, from which intention will again move it into another potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.29,0:40:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Another potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.45,0:40:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So here you see, you might say, scientifically stated, spiritual intention, its power, is via the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.45,0:40:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And the von Neumann process is a way of describing it, process one and process two.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.02,0:40:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, its significance is that Einstein is at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.02,0:40:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We said Freud was also at 499, and so was Sir Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.14,0:40:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.14,0:40:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He was confronted with this back in the 20s.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.14,0:40:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This Heisenberg process.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.18,0:40:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Refused it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.18,0:41:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He did not move, jump the paradigm jump at level 500 to the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.18,0:41:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I prefer to believe that there's an independent objective universe out there, independent of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.18,0:41:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Einstein calibrated at 499.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.32,0:41:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,David Bohm calibrates at 510.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.32,0:41:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Bohm saw the unmanifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.32,0:41:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite potential becoming manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.32,0:41:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He talked about the enfolded and unfolded universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.32,0:41:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Potential, enfolded, becoming outfolded as a consequence of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.06,0:41:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So Bohm's work calibrates about 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.69,0:41:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud, of course, made the same error when he, Freud, who is a great genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.88,0:41:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All these people at 499 are great geniuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.88,0:41:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all great geniuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.88,0:41:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud discovered the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.88,0:41:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The powerful effect of the unconscious and the fact that you don't know what's in the unconscious, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.88,0:42:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But Newton and Freud, like Einstein, just did not make the paradigm jump.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.20,0:42:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see on the calibrated level of consciousness, 500 is where you jump from a supposedly external objective logical world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.20,0:42:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to live in the subjective.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.20,0:42:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.71,0:42:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mechanistic reductionist who says nothing is real unless I can measure it and describe it scientifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.90,0:42:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the mechanistic reductionist, he says that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.90,0:42:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he say that's true?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.90,0:42:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because subjectively it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.90,0:42:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mechanistic reductionist lives in the world of subjectivity the same as the rest of us do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.90,0:42:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He talks about it in class and sounds very learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.90,0:42:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But on the way home...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.90,0:42:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.90,0:42:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.90,0:42:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's glad to see the wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.90,0:42:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not glad to see the wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.90,0:42:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's glad to see the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.90,0:42:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives in the subjective reality the same as everybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.90,0:42:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just being pompous in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.90,0:43:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to sound like a professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.22,0:43:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.22,0:43:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to give my pomposity a little shot there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.22,0:43:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.22,0:43:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, my old professor was saying, how about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.22,0:43:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.58,0:43:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.58,0:43:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we're called upon by reality, 12 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.58,0:43:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we resume?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.58,0:43:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,1.30.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.63,0:43:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.63,0:43:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,20 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.63,0:43:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, in the meantime, Susan has taught our new African gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.93,0:43:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you teach, Rockley?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.18,0:43:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, let's do kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.18,0:44:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get away from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.71,0:44:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The parrot wants me to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.75,0:44:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.75,0:44:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough of the Newtonian and the quantum mechanics and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.25,0:44:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind thinks dualistically.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.25,0:44:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks in terms of an either or.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.25,0:44:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be nonlinear?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.98,0:44:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how do you think if you're nonlinear?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.98,0:44:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't think dualistically anymore, it's against the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.98,0:44:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see that there are no opposites, that the opposite ism is a product of mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.50,0:44:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In the world, there is no opposite ism.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.50,0:44:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as we said, it's important to know because there is no opposite to truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.50,0:44:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There's either its presence or its absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.50,0:44:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Electricity is either running down the wire or it is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.50,0:44:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no alternate thing called offness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.50,0:44:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no opposite to electricity called offness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.56,0:45:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.56,0:45:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We can demonstrate this with goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.26,0:45:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And see, there's desirability.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.26,0:45:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then here, desirability gets less and less.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.26,0:45:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One variable, desirability.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.26,0:45:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take light.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.26,0:45:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, people say light and darkness are opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.06,0:45:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's light.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.06,0:45:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Light is either present or it is not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.74,0:45:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There's lots of light and then it gets dimmer and dimmer and dimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.77,0:45:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's absent.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.77,0:45:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, darkness is the absence of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.99,0:45:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.99,0:45:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's applicable, as you see, to spiritual understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.62,0:45:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The same goes, people say, well, what about hot and cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.81,0:45:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Heat is either present or not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.58,0:45:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's extremely present, which we call that very hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.28,0:45:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it's not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.28,0:45:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there is no opposite of heat in this coldness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.28,0:45:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not present.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.44,0:46:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a goodness called badness.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.21,0:46:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Value, again, you see, is just desirability.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.68,0:46:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.68,0:46:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's precious if you want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.68,0:46:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want it, it's worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.68,0:46:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it does not exist out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.68,0:46:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You project that onto it and you say, oh, how beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.29,0:46:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As you transcend all these illusions and the duality of the opposites,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.42,0:46:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,then you begin to see with increasing beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.09,0:46:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live within the field instead of the content of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.09,0:46:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,one day as you're walking along, suddenly you're struck by the incredible beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.09,0:46:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of something you catch out of the corner of your eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.09,0:46:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incredible perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.09,0:46:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's divinity radiates out to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.09,0:46:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.47,0:46:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You then notice that every weed is incredibly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.85,0:46:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at a weed and its sculpture is absolutely, incredibly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.85,0:47:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And it waves in the wind and expresses its beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.85,0:47:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The beauty of a weed is the same as the beauty of a flower,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.51,0:47:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,just of a different nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.51,0:47:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about the observer, the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.88,0:47:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We said the observer witness is faster than ten thousandths of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.88,0:47:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you live in the field rather than the content of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.07,0:47:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're talking about becomes obvious because it becomes experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.07,0:47:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to experience that everything is just the outflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.10,0:47:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This cannot be picked up by the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.05,0:47:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind picks up form.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.05,0:47:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know you have a mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.05,0:47:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it registers, you recognize it through the watcher-experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.30,0:47:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is back here that you transcend the limitation of one-tenth thousandths of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.30,0:47:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it becomes apparent that everything is just happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.30,0:48:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.30,0:48:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what is that crazy sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.30,0:48:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.30,0:48:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.30,0:48:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go on to the next exciting slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.42,0:48:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we said the power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.42,0:48:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.42,0:48:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll see how important that is when we get to brain physiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.42,0:48:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which will be coming up shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.71,0:48:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.82,0:48:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We noticed an interesting thing when we calibrated the level of the Ganges River.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.92,0:48:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ganges River is about as disgusting as you can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.92,0:48:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The sewage of one hundred large cities dumped into the Ganges River
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.01,0:48:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,dead bodies, feces, all the garbage of the world floats down the Ganges.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.01,0:48:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Ganges calibrates over five hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.01,0:48:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.01,0:48:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ganges River calibrates over five hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.01,0:49:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it has been sanctified by the collective intention of Hindus for millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.58,0:49:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ganges River calibrates over five hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.42,0:49:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just thought these are very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.42,0:49:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And to pronounce it OM, not AUM, which is an error in translation,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.48,0:49:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is an error in Satchitananda.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.48,0:49:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if it's Satchitananda's error.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.48,0:49:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Satchitananda's, I forget what it is, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.02,0:49:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,AUM is not correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.02,0:49:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,AUM is not correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.02,0:49:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Patanjali's, aphorisms of Patanjali, by Satchitananda.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.02,0:49:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.02,0:49:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pronounced AUM, and if you calibrate the difference,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.02,0:49:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there's quite a bit of difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.02,0:49:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound AUM calibrates extremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.02,0:49:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,AUM is a limitation at 210.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.02,0:49:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Om Namah Shivaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.43,0:49:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Chandi Chani Om Mani Padme Hum.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.43,0:49:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Gregorian Chants.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.43,0:50:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Japa, the Jesus Prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.43,0:50:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying the Rosary.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.20,0:50:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.65,0:50:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve-step groups calibrated 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.65,0:50:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Golden Rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.84,0:50:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See how high all these things are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.00,0:50:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the very interesting thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.00,0:50:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you notice a whole bunch of them calibrated 540,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.00,0:50:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's because of the power of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.19,0:50:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To the Western Newtonian mind, scientific mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.19,0:50:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems like rotating a prayer wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.19,0:50:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,would be an idiotic bit of ignorance, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.19,0:50:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that the intention, the intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.19,0:50:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the intention of turning the prayer wheel is 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.19,0:50:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether prayer is wafted up to heaven or not
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.19,0:50:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is all in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.19,0:50:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention is what gives it its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.48,0:50:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The wailing wall, bathing in the Ganges,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.48,0:50:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,prayer of Saint Francis of Assisi is at 580.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.48,0:50:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So devotional acts, devotional acts then.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.18,0:50:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So we sanctify things.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.18,0:51:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When we say grace in prayer, when we go thusly,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.18,0:51:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,our devotion to God at 540
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.57,0:51:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is what the power of the intention is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.57,0:51:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Power of the intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.89,0:51:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, what's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.89,0:51:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this morning it looked a little pessimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.87,0:51:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like we're really screwed up forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.87,0:51:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We've inherited an animal mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.45,0:51:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,which is all sinful from the human spiritual viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.58,0:51:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've got a prefrontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.09,0:51:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that can't tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.09,0:51:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pickle.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.18,0:51:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The human pickle
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.18,0:51:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,can't tell truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.18,0:51:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but is spiritually responsible for knowing the difference,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.18,0:51:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which it can't know by its own design.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.18,0:51:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.18,0:52:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We are screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.14,0:52:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.14,0:52:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we transcend that apparent disparity,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.14,0:52:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that duality between the animal mind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.20,0:52:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual awareness and intelligence?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.20,0:52:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said the prefrontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.20,0:52:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,produces the calibrated fields in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.20,0:52:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal produces consciousness up to 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.20,0:52:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do we ever become evolved?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.31,0:52:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because we would be sort of in a pickle forever
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.50,0:52:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,if we were limited to the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.54,0:52:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of protoplasm and causality
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.54,0:52:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the science, the dimensions of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.54,0:52:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The way out of this dilemma is non-protoplasmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.59,0:52:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not stuck just with your physical brain and your neurons.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.59,0:52:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The neurons, of course, do evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.88,0:52:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as you become more,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.88,0:52:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,more conscious and aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.88,0:52:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The neuronal configuration tends to be influenced.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.98,0:52:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The most fortuitous thing, fortunate thing for children
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.98,0:53:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is to grow up with classical music.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.98,0:53:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Classical music, exposure to some religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.98,0:53:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't make much difference which religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.01,0:53:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but some kind of a spiritual integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.79,0:53:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,exposure to classical music.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.53,0:53:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And on top of that, you can add another 1% by playing chess.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.49,0:53:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The chances of criminality,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.49,0:53:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,if you grew up under those conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.49,0:53:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is practically zilch.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.00,0:53:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The minimal...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.00,0:53:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things then bring about a neuronal patterning.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.52,0:53:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The exposure of classical music,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.65,0:53:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the classics such as the great books of the Western world,
