Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.10,1:03:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Societal problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.32,1:03:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about, this morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.32,1:03:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about the problematic hermeneutics
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.32,1:03:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.80,1:03:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we'll demonstrate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.09,1:03:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't a wicked society
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.09,1:03:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,causing the victims within it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.09,1:03:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is stratified, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.60,1:03:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stratified wherever it goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.60,1:03:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people that think
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.89,1:03:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the Taj Mahal is ugly
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.89,1:03:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bathrooms don't work well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.89,1:03:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how they experience it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.89,1:03:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's drafty and the bathrooms don't work well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.89,1:03:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wouldn't live there if you paid me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.89,1:03:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I wouldn't live there either.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.72,1:03:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Too many visitors.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.10,1:04:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.10,1:04:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are the consequence of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.10,1:04:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're the consequence of the field,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.10,1:04:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then we should see a correlation
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.10,1:04:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,between the field
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.10,1:04:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is witnessed in society.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.10,1:04:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level is 600 and over.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.84,1:04:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Rate of unemployment, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.84,1:04:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.84,1:04:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 100%.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.84,1:04:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.89,1:04:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Between consciousness level 500
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.89,1:04:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.89,1:04:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.89,1:04:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.89,1:04:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 98%.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.89,1:04:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They just broke their ankle or what,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.89,1:04:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.71,1:04:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 0.5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.71,1:04:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are fallen gurus, probably.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.71,1:04:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell tickets to heaven or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.71,1:04:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.71,1:04:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.78,1:04:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Between 400 and 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.78,1:04:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the world, the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.78,1:05:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of intellect, the great works of the worst,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.78,1:05:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.78,1:05:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,People of that level, unemployment, 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.78,1:05:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 0.5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.90,1:05:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 70%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.34,1:05:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't attended these lectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.54,1:05:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.86,1:05:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.02,1:05:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness level, 300 to 400.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.02,1:05:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good intentioned, positive emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.59,1:05:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment, 7%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.59,1:05:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're probably on unemployment insurance.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.59,1:05:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When it runs out, that'll drop to zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.26,1:05:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 1%, because they just happen to be lazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.26,1:05:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is only 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.65,1:05:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.13,1:05:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,People still, usually that's greed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.13,1:05:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Greed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.13,1:05:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At this level, it's usually, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.16,1:05:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Enron and those kind of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.48,1:05:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,WorldCom, all those kind of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.74,1:06:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.15,1:06:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we go 200 to 300.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.15,1:06:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment is still only 8%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.57,1:06:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 1.5%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.57,1:06:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness seems to be falling down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.57,1:06:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We're down to 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.79,1:06:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 9%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.14,1:06:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And now let's see what happens at consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.14,1:06:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.53,1:06:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,unemployment goes from 8% to 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.53,1:06:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,One drop in consciousness level, low 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.65,1:06:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you go from 8 to 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.65,1:06:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty goes from 1.5% to 22%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.00,1:06:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness drops from 40% to 15%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.51,1:06:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was the one we had to recheck over.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.83,1:06:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality is actually 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.83,1:06:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,People take a bribe.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.70,1:06:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,People bribe off people.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.70,1:06:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,People cheat on their income tax.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.70,1:06:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.14,1:06:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they don't feel guilt yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.14,1:07:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When you drop from 100 to 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.39,1:07:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the unemployment is 50%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.39,1:07:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 22%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.39,1:07:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is down to 15%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.39,1:07:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what happens if you drop below 100?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.39,1:07:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And a good-sized portion of society
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.39,1:07:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,does go from 50 to 100.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.46,1:07:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment is 75%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.46,1:07:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 40%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.42,1:07:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness, 2%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.51,1:07:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Criminality, 91%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.61,1:07:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,91%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.86,1:07:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get to the lower levels, below 50,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.18,1:07:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the prison populations in the United States
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.18,1:07:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate on an average from 30 to 60, around in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.18,1:07:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.18,1:07:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the criminal population below 50.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.34,1:07:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Unemployment is 97%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.36,1:07:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Poverty, 65%.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.09,1:07:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Should be higher, but they steal a lot of cars.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.45,1:08:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to treat them so I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.45,1:08:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I treated all these people.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.45,1:08:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what they're up to.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.45,1:08:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to check to see if I had my fountain pen
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.06,1:08:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when they left the office.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.06,1:08:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They just have sticky fingers.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.06,1:08:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.06,1:08:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They're living.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.38,1:08:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But their happiness rate is zero.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.38,1:08:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rate of criminality
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.92,1:08:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is all the way up to 98%.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.92,1:08:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,98%.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.92,1:08:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a consequence, then, of a level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.92,1:08:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not the fault of some segment of society
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.92,1:08:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is causing people to do these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.92,1:08:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.92,1:08:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that field.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.27,1:08:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So in that field, this is what surfaces.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.27,1:08:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this field, this is what surfaces.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.27,1:08:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.69,1:08:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.58,1:08:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What brings the figures up, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.58,1:08:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is education, intention, the things we mentioned,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.58,1:08:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the emphasis on that which is of beauty,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.68,1:09:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the beauty of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.90,1:09:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of graffiti in the New York subway.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.90,1:09:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no graffiti in the Moscow subway
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.29,1:09:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and none at all in the great cathedrals of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.51,1:09:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.67,1:09:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of the beauty is such
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.67,1:09:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you just don't think of graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.67,1:09:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Moscow subways are a beautiful, magnificent system.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.02,1:09:23.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Each subway station is like a little cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.15,1:09:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't think of graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.98,1:09:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,New York subway, graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.02,1:09:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mexico City, graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.72,1:09:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mexico City, sorry, subway calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.72,1:09:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the calibrations are in the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.72,1:09:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The subway in Mexico City calibrates the same as New York City,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.52,1:09:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,about 180 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.52,1:09:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Mexico City got, caught the idea of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.81,1:09:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in the waiting stations and the subway stations,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.81,1:09:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,they put free books.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.81,1:09:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.81,1:09:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if people are reading,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.81,1:09:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not doing graffiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.81,1:10:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So they've caught on.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.81,1:10:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to bring these bottom levels up then
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.81,1:10:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is through education,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.81,1:10:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,not by vilifying some evil doer out there,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.81,1:10:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,capitalism or the government
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.81,1:10:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or your parents or somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.84,1:10:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.84,1:10:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's just a very interesting correlation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.13,1:10:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So that sort of takes care of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.13,1:10:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.35,1:10:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought, you know, it's fun, the book I'm doing now.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.35,1:10:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can tell there's any truth in falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.48,1:10:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens if you take that and look at the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.48,1:10:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say we're coming from a different universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.48,1:10:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing we know how to do is calibrate levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.48,1:10:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We began to look over the world and see
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.74,1:10:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,if we look at levels of truth in various aspects of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.74,1:10:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,from the subway system to books to the literature
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.74,1:10:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to the great battles, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.74,1:10:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we did for fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.74,1:11:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Or she did for fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.21,1:11:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I did it for fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.21,1:11:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,She did it, but not for fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.17,1:11:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, honey, we only got 200 movies to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.17,1:11:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.20,1:11:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't know we were going to end up doing 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.20,1:11:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but we do a bunch of them, and then we think of a bunch more.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.20,1:11:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we got the most famous 100 movies ever produced.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.20,1:11:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We ended up doing 200 movies, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.20,1:11:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Show them what happened to you as a result, honey.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.20,1:11:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No good anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.48,1:11:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had to stop at 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.70,1:11:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, it's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.70,1:11:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,See, all these numerical designations can be confrontive.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.70,1:11:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a very fixed belief system
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.70,1:11:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get a calibration that doesn't coincide,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.70,1:12:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,then the thing is to look into it to understand how is it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.08,1:12:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what you're talking about is perception,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.08,1:12:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're just calibrating things
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.08,1:12:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what is their intrinsic reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.08,1:12:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So move to the next, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.72,1:12:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them you would just guess by looking at them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.72,1:12:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are so ghastly, I would never even see them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.72,1:12:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say, what's that about?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.72,1:12:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God, I don't even hear what it's about.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.72,1:12:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just go see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.72,1:12:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to subject myself to that energy field, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.39,1:12:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.39,1:12:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so what if we calibrate the world?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.46,1:12:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have we got today?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.46,1:12:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot this.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.46,1:12:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There's 40 to this, and we're at 120.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.46,1:12:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,133.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.42,1:12:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Break.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.61,1:12:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that three?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.61,1:12:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Another hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.61,1:12:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.61,1:12:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.98,1:12:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens then if we're from another planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.98,1:12:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and we want to know what, before we land on this planet,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.98,1:12:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we going to encounter?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.98,1:13:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So one thing you can do from a different culture
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.08,1:13:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is calibrate the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.08,1:13:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.21,1:13:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see, we said America runs about 421,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.24,1:13:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but the northern, north, this continent,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.24,1:13:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this continent,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.24,1:13:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this whole hemisphere is a very lucky hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.24,1:13:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the right side of the world to get born on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.24,1:13:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd advise it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.24,1:13:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you come back to this world, pick this hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.65,1:13:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,America's 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.65,1:13:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But generally it runs 415, 410,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.65,1:13:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,various like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.81,1:13:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,South America, Caribbean islands.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.81,1:13:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You see South America's in good shape.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.81,1:13:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's close up around 300s,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.81,1:13:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a very good place to live.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.81,1:13:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then right in the middle of this,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.81,1:13:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you have the anachronism of Haiti at 55.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.81,1:13:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking this morning about group karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.77,1:13:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, group karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.77,1:13:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So these people must have a group karma
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.77,1:14:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,coming in at 55.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.77,1:14:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course they celebrate,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.77,1:14:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, they do voodoo and blood sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.77,1:14:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and worship demons and things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.77,1:14:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that may be a concomitant
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.77,1:14:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of being at level 55.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.77,1:14:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,55 is not a threat to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.90,1:14:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,55 is too incapacitated by its own internal problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.90,1:14:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They're lucky if they have enough to eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.90,1:14:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think there's been 20 different attempts
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.31,1:14:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to raise the level of consciousness in Haiti,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.31,1:14:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and none of them has succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.31,1:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems like a karmic propensity, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.60,1:14:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right in the middle of a hemisphere like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.60,1:14:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you suddenly have a pocket
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.60,1:14:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that all calibrates at a certain level.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.60,1:14:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange and peculiar.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.76,1:14:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.69,1:14:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a different way of deepening.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.69,1:14:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We're depicting this hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.69,1:14:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Greenland, Canada, Alaska.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.85,1:14:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that Alaska up there?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.85,1:14:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that over there?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.26,1:15:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Alaska, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.78,1:15:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mexico, the Caribbean.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.78,1:15:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty much the same thing we saw before.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.78,1:15:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just delineated Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.78,1:15:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are good countries.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.78,1:15:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in the positive emotions, above 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.78,1:15:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we go to the other hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.99,1:15:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, I would pick the first hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.99,1:15:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the second one to get reborn.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.66,1:15:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This hemisphere is Australia at 410.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.66,1:15:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see China.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.70,1:15:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,China has come up a long way.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.70,1:15:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,China has come up a long way.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.24,1:15:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Manchuria.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.24,1:15:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see India.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.30,1:15:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You see vast Russia.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.30,1:15:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you look over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.30,1:15:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's India.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.30,1:15:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see Africa and Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.37,1:15:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.37,1:15:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you can expect
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.37,1:15:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all these.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.40,1:15:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Here in the middle of Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.40,1:15:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you got a calibrated level of life at 40.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.75,1:15:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,40, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.75,1:16:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,40.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.14,1:16:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What does 40 come forth as?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.14,1:16:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Rwanda, Civil War, Sudan, starvation, AIDS,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.51,1:16:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,massacres, tribal warfare between chieftains, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.51,1:16:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,However, they're overwhelmed with their own internal problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.66,1:16:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no threat to the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.66,1:16:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They can barely get by till tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.76,1:16:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then as you get north,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.76,1:16:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to North Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.76,1:16:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,now you begin to see
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.76,1:16:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,their rising of difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.76,1:16:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see Europe in the 300s to 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.76,1:16:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Scandinavia,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.76,1:16:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all doing quite well.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.76,1:16:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't expect any trouble from Japan either.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.75,1:16:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're looking for where you're going to find trouble,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.75,1:16:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to find it here in Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.75,1:16:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially you're going to find it in North Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.75,1:16:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't know anything about the news,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.75,1:16:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,never read it,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.75,1:16:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I can look at this map
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.75,1:16:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell you where there's going to be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.75,1:17:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because 170, 180, 190 now has enough energy to it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.75,1:17:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that it can do a lot of harm.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.75,1:17:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, both sides,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.26,1:17:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in endless conflicts,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.71,1:17:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to calibrate about 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.71,1:17:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride, pride, arrogance,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.71,1:17:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,eye for an eye, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.78,1:17:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness is not in the,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.78,1:17:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiveness is not part of
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.81,1:17:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,energy fuels 180 or 190.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.81,1:17:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can forecast then
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.81,1:17:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the likelihood of what goes on.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.81,1:17:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be where
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.90,1:17:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Rwanda and Sudan, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.90,1:17:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a more detailed map.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.90,1:17:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so detailed you can't read it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.90,1:17:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.18,1:17:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we took this one out.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.18,1:17:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It escaped.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.73,1:17:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw the distribution of the levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.73,1:17:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the prior map we correlated them
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.14,1:17:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with crime, poverty, income, education, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.14,1:17:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just the distribution
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.14,1:18:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of AIDS in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.14,1:18:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see the distribution of AIDS
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.14,1:18:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is almost identical to the map we just looked at.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.72,1:18:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The distribution of AIDS then
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.72,1:18:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,correlates with level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.62,1:18:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not caused by anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.98,1:18:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The calibration level of 70 to 90
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.72,1:18:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,gives you no karmic immunity
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.72,1:18:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to a negativity, whatever it might be.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.72,1:18:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If this was closer to the middle ages,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.72,1:18:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd be looking at the distribution
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.72,1:18:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Black Death and the Plague.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.88,1:18:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This would be the distribution map
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.88,1:18:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Black Plague instead of AIDS.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.88,1:18:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But AIDS is today's Black Plague.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.88,1:18:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so, move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.70,1:18:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the broken window principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.70,1:18:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy attracts to it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.70,1:18:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is concordant with that energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.59,1:18:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's important to raise
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.59,1:19:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the level of consciousness of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.59,1:19:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To pick up the trash on the streets.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.94,1:19:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.94,1:19:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Eliminate crime so long as there's trash
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.94,1:19:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,on the streets. Not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.94,1:19:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they come from the same energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.07,1:19:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That which doesn't care enough
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.23,1:19:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,about its own environment,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.23,1:19:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that which doesn't care about its fellow human being,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.23,1:19:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that which doesn't care about
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.23,1:19:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,neatness, orderliness, beauty,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.23,1:19:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,then desecrates beauty
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.58,1:19:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and it throws its trash on the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.58,1:19:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Not my problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.87,1:19:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They get paid to clean it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.87,1:19:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you see trash on the streets,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.15,1:19:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell you what the crime rate is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.15,1:19:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell you what the crime rate is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.95,1:19:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We can go blindfolded.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.59,1:19:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Any street, any city in the United States,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.59,1:19:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,any world, look at the street
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.59,1:19:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell you what the crime rate is there.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.59,1:19:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.10,1:19:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're looking at war and peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.10,1:19:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're looking at history.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.42,1:19:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to discern what is the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.42,1:20:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of what value might this be
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.42,1:20:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in establishing peace as a reality
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.42,1:20:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,other than just a political slogan.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.42,1:20:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, peace is a political slogan.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.49,1:20:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And people who really want it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.49,1:20:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't do it for a price.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.49,1:20:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wonderful political slogan.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.71,1:20:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So most people who talk about peace
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.71,1:20:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,are talking about it as a political do-gooderism
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.71,1:20:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to win something or other.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.71,1:20:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't really mean it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.71,1:20:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a war,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.96,1:20:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,well documented in history,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.96,1:20:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,about which there is no currently unfolding mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.96,1:20:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, pretty much settled
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.50,1:20:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and pretty much
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.50,1:20:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,concordance of opinion about this war.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.50,1:20:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we discover about a war
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.73,1:20:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that's applicable to today's world
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.73,1:20:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and to the peace in the future?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.73,1:20:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that one of the greatest powers
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.82,1:20:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in the World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.82,1:20:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was the heart of Winston Churchill,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.82,1:21:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the heart of the lion.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.82,1:21:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the heart of the lion at 510
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.30,1:21:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that held together the British people,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.30,1:21:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,held them together, the heart of the lion.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.68,1:21:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Roosevelt at 499,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.68,1:21:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,later Truman, General Eisenhower, MacArthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.00,1:21:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The U.S. government at 395,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.00,1:21:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in the norm of the invasion.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.22,1:21:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Heisenberg,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.63,1:21:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which came the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.63,1:21:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wernher von Braun,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.63,1:21:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the U.S. military.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.63,1:21:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's something we were talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.63,1:21:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at lunch, triage.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.63,1:21:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Triage in the essence of,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.63,1:21:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in the context of the Second World War,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.63,1:21:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated at 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.63,1:21:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The dropping of the atomic bomb
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.63,1:21:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was triage.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.02,1:21:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Not understood by.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.02,1:21:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind doesn't understand triage
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.18,1:21:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,until you get to consciousness level 360.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.18,1:21:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's understandable in the military.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.53,1:21:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not understandable.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.53,1:21:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacrifice of the few for the many.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.04,1:22:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.12,1:22:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Having to pick the lesser of two evils.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.12,1:22:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we look at the dropping of the atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.12,1:22:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,President Truman had to decide
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.12,1:22:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to sacrifice 7 million,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.50,1:22:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the estimated death rate if we invaded Japan,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.50,1:22:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was 7 million.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.50,1:22:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,6 million Japanese and 1 million Americans
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.54,1:22:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,against killing 180,000 innocent civilians.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.98,1:22:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Triage, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.98,1:22:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is to try to save life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.02,1:22:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Politically it's demonized as killing life.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.39,1:22:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You got your choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.28,1:22:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,7 million or 180,000?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.44,1:22:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So Truman,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.44,1:22:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we can get what Truman's intention was
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.44,1:22:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and what his level of...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.44,1:22:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,intention was at 495.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.73,1:22:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He was pushing the intellect
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.73,1:22:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to do what he thought was best for the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.73,1:22:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You can disagree with him,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.73,1:23:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's what it calibrates at.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.50,1:23:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we have the German military,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.59,1:23:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the military command.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.59,1:23:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the military are usually quite integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.59,1:23:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, very often the military
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.59,1:23:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate higher than the generals.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.59,1:23:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The generals were willing to sacrifice...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.59,1:23:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler was willing to sacrifice the whole German army
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.59,1:23:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and, in fact, all the German people, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.62,1:23:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So U.S. military at Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.94,1:23:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kamikaze pilots calibrate quite high
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.94,1:23:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and so does the Luftwaffe.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.94,1:23:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we saw Emperor Hirohito at 200
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.49,1:23:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and Admiral Yamamoto.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.49,1:23:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get a chance to look over
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.62,1:23:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what are the facts involved.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.65,1:23:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler at 45.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.65,1:23:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we're going to prevent war in the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.68,1:23:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then we better use consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.68,1:23:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibration techniques
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.68,1:23:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to diagnose the situation
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.68,1:23:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,before we decide on a course of action.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.68,1:23:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So at least you know what you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.68,1:24:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Adolf Hitler by that time was down to 45.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.90,1:24:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Stalin was down to 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.90,1:24:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All these dictators are all the way down.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.90,1:24:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And faithfully and unfortunately for the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.44,1:24:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobel Chamberlain calibrated at 185.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.44,1:24:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When he negotiated a peace treaty with Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.49,1:24:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and came home with a news piece on our time,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.29,1:24:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler thought he was a stupid idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.61,1:24:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.31,1:24:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sucker, how dumb can you get?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.38,1:24:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Like signing a contract with the mafia.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.38,1:24:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay you back a quarter of a million Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.38,1:24:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.38,1:24:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.38,1:24:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.38,1:24:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.63,1:24:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the Third Reich.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.63,1:24:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Neville Chamberlain said in denial
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.63,1:24:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,he was suffering from the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.50,1:25:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,impairment of crippled hermeneutics
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.54,1:25:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of relativistic epistemology.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.54,1:25:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Deadly.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.20,1:25:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's deadly, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.20,1:25:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.20,1:25:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese embassy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.20,1:25:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese government.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.20,1:25:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Robin Rappenheimer early was an integrist.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.26,1:25:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Late he sold out, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.26,1:25:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,League of Nations didn't do too good at 185.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.36,1:25:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pacifists attack up Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.36,1:25:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can analyze everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.35,1:25:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the Cambridge Five.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.35,1:25:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is why we actually ended up with the Iraqi War.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.35,1:25:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The Iraqi War was a fear of atomic power.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.35,1:25:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Atomic power.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.35,1:25:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.35,1:25:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In the hands of the wrong people.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.35,1:25:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And how did the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.35,1:25:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,how did the secret of the atomic bomb get out?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.35,1:25:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The secret of the atomic bomb was sold out
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.58,1:25:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by these people here.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.22,1:26:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These people sold us out.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.79,1:26:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Americans who turned against their own country
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.79,1:26:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,with pseudo-philosophic,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.79,1:26:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,pseudo-spiritual argumentation,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.79,1:26:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is nothing but intellectual egotism.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.79,1:26:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So we were sold out then.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.95,1:26:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And because of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.95,1:26:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is in current danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.95,1:26:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the minute we suspect a rogue nation
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.95,1:26:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,has atomic power,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.95,1:26:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,all hell breaks loose.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.05,1:26:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All hell breaks loose.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.05,1:26:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because of the reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.34,1:26:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but because of the potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.34,1:26:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have access to atomic secrets.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.34,1:26:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And where did they get them?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.34,1:26:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm showing you where they came from.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.62,1:26:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They came from this guy who turned against.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.23,1:26:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It came from the intellectuals
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.68,1:26:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the Cambridge Five.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.68,1:26:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it got to Russia.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.71,1:26:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And Russia was a serious threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.54,1:26:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.54,1:26:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because its intention was less than 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.54,1:26:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but its capability was over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.61,1:27:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Its capability was over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.61,1:27:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And its intention was below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.61,1:27:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is the danger sign.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.61,1:27:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless society learns that,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.77,1:27:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,war will be with us forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.77,1:27:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the practical application?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.02,1:27:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Is spirituality just airy-fairy?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.02,1:27:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual truth, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.41,1:27:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in daily life,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.76,1:27:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is manifest as integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.66,1:27:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't talk about Jesus and Buddha
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.42,1:27:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and holiness and all that in the secular world.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.58,1:27:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But the beginning of spiritual responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.58,1:27:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is truth and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.58,1:27:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So the alignment with truth, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.58,1:27:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is not called, labeled spirituality
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.58,1:27:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ordinary world.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.58,1:27:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is the beginning of real power.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.58,1:27:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning of real power.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.10,1:28:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And looking at the history of the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.10,1:28:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in completing this book,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.10,1:28:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,several years in which we did 7,000 calibrations,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.10,1:28:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,everything in history and current and past life,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.10,1:28:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing became apparent.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.93,1:28:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest enemy to peace in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.30,1:28:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is political naivete
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.30,1:28:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the clumsiness, awkwardness, and fallacy
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.03,1:28:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of international diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.03,1:28:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely no sense to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.35,1:28:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,no reason to it, no logic to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.35,1:28:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,much less a science to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.35,1:28:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There could be no hope of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.83,1:28:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so long as people are dealing with falsehood and illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.15,1:28:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dictum of which we speak
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.15,1:28:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is that truth brings peace
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.70,1:28:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and falsehood brings war.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.70,1:28:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot have war without falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.70,1:28:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's built upon falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.70,1:28:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor can you have peace without truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.70,1:28:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So to establish that, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.73,1:28:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have to know what is the difference
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.73,1:28:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,between truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.73,1:28:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And inasmuch as the human mind innately
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.73,1:28:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is incapable of that,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.73,1:28:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see why the history of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.73,1:29:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,has been what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.88,1:29:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 7% of the time
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.54,1:29:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of human history
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.54,1:29:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,has there been peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.54,1:29:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,7%.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.58,1:29:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,93% of human history
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.58,1:29:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,has always been a war.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.58,1:29:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In my lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.12,1:29:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there's already five or six of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.12,1:29:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many wars
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.12,1:29:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lost track of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.70,1:29:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,World War I had just stopped.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.70,1:29:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We're into World War II.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.73,1:29:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the Korean War, Vietnam War,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.73,1:29:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and go for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.73,1:29:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's half a dozen wars
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.73,1:29:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,just in one lifetime, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.73,1:29:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So peace is something
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.79,1:29:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,other than a placard
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.79,1:29:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and a protest march.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.89,1:29:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is based on radical science.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.89,1:29:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Radical science of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.89,1:29:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I put together this
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.23,1:29:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,for the sake of internet
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.23,1:29:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and international diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.95,1:30:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard interviews on television
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.95,1:30:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that to me were shocking
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.95,1:30:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,where an interviewer
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.82,1:30:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,mockingly suggests
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.82,1:30:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to the president
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.82,1:30:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of the largest country in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.82,1:30:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the oldest countries in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.82,1:30:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,6,000 years of civilization
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.82,1:30:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,before America was even thought of,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.82,1:30:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's telling him
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.82,1:30:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that he ought to really correct
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.82,1:30:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,his internal affairs in his country.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.82,1:30:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was so shockingly rude.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.82,1:30:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.82,1:30:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.19,1:30:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The president of China is already,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.19,1:30:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,now there's a different one,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.19,1:30:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but the president of China at that time
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.19,1:30:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated around 455.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.19,1:30:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.70,1:30:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we put together then
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.70,1:30:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,some kind of a science
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.70,1:30:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of international diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.73,1:30:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's never been such a thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.73,1:30:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.05,1:30:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,never been a science
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.05,1:30:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of international diplomacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.05,1:30:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't just do international diplomacy
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.05,1:30:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by votes, tarot cards,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.18,1:30:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.18,1:31:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,channeled information.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.18,1:31:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.18,1:31:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So this chart is called Us and Them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.18,1:31:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's useful in many applications.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.18,1:31:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we're just talking about it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.18,1:31:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was the implication
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.18,1:31:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for world peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.18,1:31:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called the Us and Them chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.18,1:31:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be your company
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.37,1:31:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and other companies.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.37,1:31:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be your company
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.37,1:31:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and your target market.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.37,1:31:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be your government association.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.37,1:31:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be your part
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.37,1:31:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in civil organizations.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.65,1:31:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be the local towns,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.65,1:31:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be your own meeting.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.65,1:31:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be any place in our world
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.78,1:31:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,where you have two different segments
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.78,1:31:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of society dealing with each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.97,1:31:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And this chart is called Us and Them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.97,1:31:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Us and Them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.97,1:31:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives you some kind of a scientific
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.97,1:31:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,rational basis upon which
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.97,1:31:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to approach other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.00,1:31:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,First you have to know who you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.00,1:31:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then you have to know who them is.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.00,1:31:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody in this world knows who they are,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.25,1:31:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,much less who them is.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.63,1:32:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you have success?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.63,1:32:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know who you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.11,1:32:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.11,1:32:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.20,1:32:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,After many years of psychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.20,1:32:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew who I was.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.45,1:32:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It was now my job,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.45,1:32:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when a patient walked in,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.45,1:32:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.45,1:32:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't their job
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.45,1:32:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to come to where I was.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.45,1:32:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my job to go where they were
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.45,1:32:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and build a walkway between us.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.06,1:32:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so this is Us.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.06,1:32:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In international politics,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.06,1:32:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a profound application
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.06,1:32:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of really new science,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.31,1:32:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,this is Us.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.54,1:32:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is Them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.70,1:32:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the calibrated levels
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.70,1:32:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.70,1:32:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and sort of the predominant
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.18,1:32:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,emotional field.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.18,1:32:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hear me talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.18,1:32:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my gosh, I can hear myself
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.18,1:32:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.18,1:32:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.34,1:32:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,My voice goes out the front of my head
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.34,1:32:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and comes in the back of my head.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.34,1:32:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.50,1:32:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That was wonderful, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.50,1:32:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.33,1:32:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can even hear what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.33,1:33:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so here we have
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.33,1:33:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,America at 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.33,1:33:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here's who we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.09,1:33:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of dumbly,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.09,1:33:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,walk through the world
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.28,1:33:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,telling everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.28,1:33:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they ought to be democratic.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.28,1:33:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You should have a democracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.28,1:33:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should they have a democracy?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.47,1:33:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because you think
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.47,1:33:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a good idea, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.47,1:33:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we are at 421,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.04,1:33:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and here is where
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.04,1:33:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the other country is.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.04,1:33:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what is their language?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.04,1:33:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our job is to know
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.42,1:33:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what their language is,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.42,1:33:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,not vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.42,1:33:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They aren't evolved enough
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.42,1:33:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to even be interested
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.42,1:33:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in this chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.42,1:33:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the people of America
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.96,1:33:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,are probably not interested in it,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.96,1:33:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're going to get it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.15,1:33:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we are at 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.50,1:33:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you look at
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.50,1:33:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.50,1:33:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty safe dealing
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.50,1:34:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with Canadians
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.50,1:34:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,despite their politics.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.50,1:34:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They believe in what they believe,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.50,1:34:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't know they're stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.50,1:34:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.50,1:34:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.79,1:34:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,now you see
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.79,1:34:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,where is the other country
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.79,1:34:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you're dealing with, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.79,1:34:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Central Africa
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.79,1:34:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,at 40 to 80.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.79,1:34:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky to get through
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.43,1:34:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,a single day alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.43,1:34:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're awake at 8 in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.43,1:34:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you're lucky to be alive
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.43,1:34:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,at 4 in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.62,1:34:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If starvation,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.62,1:34:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,lack of water,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.62,1:34:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,deprivation,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.62,1:34:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,disease,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.62,1:34:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,marauding tribal chieftains
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.62,1:34:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from neighboring tribes
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.62,1:34:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't chopped you up yet,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.62,1:34:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you're lucky to still be breathing.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.72,1:34:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.72,1:34:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.39,1:34:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you look at the Middle East.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.39,1:34:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it runs around 180 to 190,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.62,1:34:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and those are the levels of pride,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.98,1:34:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,militant pride and getting even.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.30,1:35:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A tit for a tat,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.30,1:35:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,an eye for an eye,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.30,1:35:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and forgiveness is not something
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.30,1:35:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you can expect of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.30,1:35:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgiveness is up around 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.72,1:35:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.33,1:35:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at China in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.33,1:35:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,South America.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.42,1:35:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.65,1:35:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the context?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.65,1:35:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What is reality
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.65,1:35:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to the people we're talking to?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.65,1:35:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason appeals to Canadians, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.87,1:35:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It appeals to Canadians.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.16,1:35:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not appeal to the Middle East.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.16,1:35:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrogance and pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.31,1:35:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We kill a busload of children,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.89,1:35:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they kill a busload of children.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.89,1:35:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We blow up a busload
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.89,1:35:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of their diplomats,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.89,1:35:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they blow up a busload.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.89,1:35:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,An eye for an eye
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.89,1:35:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and a tit for a tat.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.14,1:35:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know what to expect.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.14,1:35:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What to expect of who you're dealing with
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.14,1:35:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore you know how to appeal to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.14,1:36:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultures that are coming from lack
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.51,1:36:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,would only be interested in what we offer
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.51,1:36:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a gain to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.09,1:36:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming from the solar plexus.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.09,1:36:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear about democracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.47,1:36:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in it for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.47,1:36:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in it for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.92,1:36:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.04,1:36:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Solar plexus is me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.04,1:36:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in it for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.42,1:36:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Democracy is great.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.42,1:36:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's in it for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.42,1:36:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I vote for it?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.42,1:36:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's equality?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.42,1:36:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.49,1:36:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Countries like that think that's such a stupid idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.49,1:36:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.71,1:36:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality, giving votes, equality to women,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.71,1:36:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the lower classes, never mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.63,1:36:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're called dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.76,1:36:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In their own society,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.76,1:36:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,their own citizens are called dogs
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.76,1:36:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,by their rulers.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.76,1:36:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.76,1:36:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler was willing to kill them all
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.34,1:36:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because they lost the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.34,1:36:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There is dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.34,1:37:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Saddam Hussein called them dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.34,1:37:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,These people here see women, children, and dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.49,1:37:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.74,1:37:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you give these women a vote?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.74,1:37:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What, dogs?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.86,1:37:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Women and children and dogs
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.86,1:37:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,are down at the bottom in such a society.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.86,1:37:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to know who you're talking to now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.86,1:37:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that these people here are ruled by reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.12,1:37:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,These are into willingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.12,1:37:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all of South America.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.12,1:37:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got very willing people.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.12,1:37:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're willing to go along with whatever they think is good.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.12,1:37:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you've got neutral.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.12,1:37:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you've got courage.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.12,1:37:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But from here on down, you're dealing in pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.12,1:37:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is North Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.12,1:37:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is South, Central Africa.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.15,1:37:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is true now of any political situation in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.08,1:37:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,economic situation,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.08,1:37:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're a giant business,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.08,1:37:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a giant corporation,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.08,1:38:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're dealing with a new market.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.01,1:38:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you appeal to that market?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.33,1:38:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That they should buy your product
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.33,1:38:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because your product is so wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.33,1:38:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.33,1:38:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How would it appeal to them?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.49,1:38:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How would it appeal to them?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.49,1:38:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends completely on your level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.74,1:38:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and their level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.74,1:38:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, out of facing the facts,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:22.74,1:38:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,facing the facts.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.94,1:38:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we fantasize about this country.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.94,1:38:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We fantasize about these cultures.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.94,1:38:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.94,1:38:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so if you want to calibrate a culture,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.42,1:38:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a country,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.42,1:38:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you need to know?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.42,1:38:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to know three calibrations.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.42,1:38:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We only showed one today.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.54,1:38:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to know the calibration of the ruler.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.74,1:38:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to know that Saddam Hussein calibrates at 75.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.74,1:38:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,At 75, we'll kill you for a buck.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:50.79,1:38:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have to know the calibration of the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.36,1:38:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The government.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.36,1:39:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We know countries where the people are fantastic,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.36,1:39:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the leaders fantastic,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.36,1:39:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the government is so rotten,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.36,1:39:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you take your life in your hands if you drive across the border.
