Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.70,1:52:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs those who uplift society by virtue of that which you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.83,1:52:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, your life becomes, as I've said before,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.05,1:52:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your life becomes a mudra.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:42.43,1:52:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, in spiritual language, a mudra is a sacred position.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.74,1:52:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is attacked by many people in sort of a yang kind of a fashion.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:57.12,1:53:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to go after enlightenment and battle their way to it
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.12,1:53:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,through fasts and shaving your head in sandals and walking about in the desert,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:09.25,1:53:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,pilgrimages to various places.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.28,1:53:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:13.28,1:53:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the yang way of approaching it.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.52,1:53:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you embrace that which is integrous and become it,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.51,1:53:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,then your life becomes like a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.38,1:53:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And the spiritual revelation is very yin.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.95,1:53:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One steps back from positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:53:38.43,1:53:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and allows the reality to reveal itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.43,1:53:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which it does unbidden.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:46.43,1:53:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Of its own, it reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:50.20,1:53:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As you're walking down the street,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:52.20,1:53:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you notice the incredible beauty of the weed.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.20,1:54:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, one day you see its sculpture is absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.42,1:54:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One person could create such a sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.06,1:54:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be coming out of the divinity within them
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.06,1:54:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because beauty is the essence of spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:15.06,1:54:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as love and forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.06,1:54:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and kindness, sharing, tenderness.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.43,1:54:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we understand sort of a science of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.85,1:54:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,now we can see where everyone is in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.85,1:54:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see the innate innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:54:36.85,1:54:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of those who are born for whatever karmic propensities
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.30,1:54:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill whatever karmic destinies
Dialogue: 0,1:54:44.30,1:54:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,via the Rig Veda, let us say,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.49,1:54:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,which teaches that
Dialogue: 0,1:54:48.49,1:54:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that which gives up its life for a higher life
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.35,1:54:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,earns the karmic right to become that higher life.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.02,1:55:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When you sacrifice yourself to thee,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.25,1:55:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,then you become entitled to become that.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.27,1:55:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So what seems to us as needless sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.27,1:55:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is from a very limited egoistic perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:17.27,1:55:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see are people proceeding
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.18,1:55:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to the realization of their own divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:28.50,1:55:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What you see is the unfolding of the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.50,1:55:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to undo the bad karma of that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.10,1:55:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the undoing of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:39.10,1:55:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the essence of it
Dialogue: 0,1:55:41.10,1:55:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of that comes the forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.10,1:55:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that comes the forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.10,1:55:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of that one's energy field advances.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.14,1:55:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it is not necessary to demonize
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.10,1:55:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,any aspect of life
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.10,1:55:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because all of life subserves
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.10,1:56:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole, all of life subserves the whole.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.74,1:56:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of us serve life
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.74,1:56:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,by appearing to be sacrificed in the process.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.14,1:56:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking at lunch about the Rig Veda,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.68,1:56:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which points out that through sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.00,1:56:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,through surrender,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.30,1:56:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is lower life
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.30,1:56:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,earns its life to become higher life,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:25.37,1:56:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,which the Native American realized
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.37,1:56:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,when he sacrifices the life of the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:30.91,1:56:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The Native American,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.91,1:56:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,whose spirituality he calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.91,1:56:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely high from, by the way,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.42,1:56:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,intuited the attractor field
Dialogue: 0,1:56:40.42,1:56:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and could even visualize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.42,1:56:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The attractor field,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:44.42,1:56:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the core of a certain animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.42,1:56:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,See, each animal kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:50.42,1:56:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the animals all have the same attractor field,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.42,1:56:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,this powerful attractor field then.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.42,1:57:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So all mules, all horses, all cats, all dogs
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.70,1:57:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,have the same
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.70,1:57:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,central organizing energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.80,1:57:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't have individual karma yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:11.80,1:57:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Native American intuited
Dialogue: 0,1:57:13.80,1:57:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and even saw in their visions
Dialogue: 0,1:57:16.80,1:57:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field, the attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.80,1:57:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Natives who worship the,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:22.80,1:57:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or pray to the spirit of the tiger,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:28.34,1:57:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit of the tiger does rule the forest.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:32.46,1:57:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the tiger rules the forest.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:34.46,1:57:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:36.46,1:57:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The tiger is the king of the forest.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.28,1:57:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the Native American then
Dialogue: 0,1:57:45.54,1:57:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,kills in order for a higher life to evolve,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:49.54,1:57:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,what it does is it sanctifies
Dialogue: 0,1:57:51.54,1:57:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the sacrifice of the animal,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.82,1:57:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which by its being sanctified,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.82,1:58:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it gives up its life for thee, O human,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.82,1:58:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and by virtue of my sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,1:58:04.82,1:58:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,do I earn becoming one of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:09.89,1:58:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the former tiger in me speaking.
